## The *SUPPRESSED* mark represents our work to control personal exposure in systems that collect, index, republish, and regenerate personal information.

These guidelines explain how our name, marks, logos, product names, graphics, and brand assets may be referenced. They are intended to protect the brand while allowing accurate references to the company, our services, and our work.

The brand is a valuable intellectual property asset. To preserve the trust attached to it, the mark must be used clearly, accurately, and in a way that does not suggest an affiliation, endorsement, partnership, or approval that does not exist.

Nothing on this page grants a license, assignment, transfer, or other right to use our intellectual property except as expressly stated.

